                  <persName id="t18311201-275-person2076">
                  SARAH 
                  ANN RISEBOROUGH
               <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2076" type="surname" value="ANN RISEBOROUGH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2076" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2076" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Mr. Collins' shop, opposite <placeName id="t18311201-275-crimeloc1465">the Grove, at Hackney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-275-crimeloc1465" type="placeName" value="the Grove, at Hackney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-275-crimeloc1465" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-275-off1463 t18311201-275-crimeloc1465"></join>, on the 1st of December, and saw the prisoner take a cloak from the door, and run away with it; I informed the shopman, who pursued - he was taken to the station-house; I saw him there, and can positively state he is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-275-person2077">
                  ROBERT 
                  TURNER FRY
               <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2077" type="surname" value="TURNER FRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2077" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2077" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 1st of December I saw the prisoner running from the door; I followed him, and called Stop thief! he then turned a corner, and I lost sight<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183112010116"></xptr>of him - he was then stopped by a gentleman; I saw him throw the cloak away - it was brought to me by Tyndale.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-275-person2078">
                  JOHN 
                  RENSHAM
               <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2078" type="surname" value="RENSHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2078" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2078" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was walking up the Grove, and saw several persons struggling; I made up to them - Fry gave me the prisoner and this cloak.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-275-person2079">
                  THOMAS 
                  TYNDALE
               <interp inst="t18311201-275-person2079" type="surname" value="TYNDALE"></interp>
